                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="460942" author="adilger" created="Mon, 23 Jun 2025 22:19:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/38938&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/38938&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12549&quot; title=&quot;Lustre project PID 32-bit overflow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12549&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12549&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; utils: Check range of quota ID for &quot;lfs&quot; arguments&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) changing to use &lt;tt&gt;str2quotaid()&lt;/tt&gt; that assumes all input is base-10 (as all other quota commands did, except &lt;tt&gt;lfs_project()&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="441834" author="adilger" created="Tue, 21 Jan 2025 18:53:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I checked that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;useradd -u 010000&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is creating the account with decimal 10000 UID/GID, and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;chown 010000:010000 /tmp/foo&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is setting decimal 10000 UID/GID on the file, so it makes sense to be consistent with the common commands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
